rehensively characterized as a unified school of "ethical socialism." By showing that they varied fundamentally regarding their political views and their philosophical foundations of socialism, Widmer fills a gap in the studies of neo-Kantianism that is long overdue.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aAlternativen zum Marxismus. 4aGeschichte der westlichen Philosophie. 4aNeo-Kantianismus. 4asoziales und politisches Denken. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aNeo-Kantianism.  aalternatives to Marxism.  ahistory of western philosophy.  asocial and political thought.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023 Englishz978311131922308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023z9783111318646oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831113319040 cprintz978311133177540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783111331843zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111331843zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111331843/original  a978-3-11-131922-3 EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DPHb2023  aZDB-23-GOA